We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:

a) instruct the General Services Officer to process all purchasing concerns and the keeping of records to keep track of the movement of stocks on hand from receipt until issuance for accounting, control and accountability purposes;

b) consider the provision of  storage so that the procurement of  supplies  in significant quantity can be stored to lessen the administrative cost in frequent procurements and reimbursements;

c) require the General Services Officer to (i)  prepare and submit documents on purchases of the Municipality; (ii) prepare and maintain stock cards for the purchased supplies; (iii) conduct periodic inventory of supplies as prescribed by the above regulation; and (iv) procure, as far as practicable and feasible, directly from the DBM-PS all anticipated common-use supplies, and resort to local suppliers only upon unavailability of supplies needed; and

d) require the Acting Municipal Accountant to (i) ensure that the required documentary requirements supporting the purchase transactions are attached; (ii) process only claims that are properly signed and approved/certified by the authorized officials; (iii) henceforth recognize all purchase of supplies and materials under the proper inventory account; (ii) prepare supplies ledger cards for delivered items as provided by the above quoted regulation.

