(ii) as head of the MDC, fast track the preparation of the Municipality’s Comprehensive Development Plan (CDP) and Comprehensive Land-Use Plan (CLUP) in order that disaster risk management activities could be integrated to the development plan of the Municipality to prevent loss of lives and properties;    

Members of the MDRRMC (i) institute the functional organization of the ICS, the required training and resource management which include the personnel, teams, equipment, and other facilities available during emergencies, as a perfect tool in responding to all types of hazards most particularly in an on-scene emergency situations and calamities such as flooding; (ii) ensure that the member CSOs/NGOs to the Council possess the eligibility requirements cited under NDRRMC No.  3 to ensure effective and strengthened citizen’s participation in the locality;

MDRRMO prepare the monthly report on the sources and utilization of the LDRMMF and facilitate monitoring of the accomplishment vis-à-vis targeted projects for effective and efficient utilization of the Fund; and

Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer (i) facilitate the transfer of unexpended balance of the LDRMF to the Trust Fund accounts; and (ii) install an effective internal control in the recording, maintenance and distribution of relief items and disaster response equipment in accordance with the above-mentioned rules and regulations.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive 

a) order the immediate installation of the donated equipment and utilize the same for the purpose for which they were donated when the construction of the material recovery facility is completed. Meantime that they are still idle, ensure the proper storage thereof to prevent deterioration;

b) coordinate efforts with the barangay officials on the implementation of the five basic environmental laws on preserving and protecting the environment required under R.A. No. 9003;  

c) request the Municipal Solid Waste Management Board to prioritize the finalization of the ten-year SWMP for the early identification of issues/gaps in complying with RA No. 9003 and the prompt resolution thereof; and 

d) initiate intensive information drive and awareness campaign on solid waste management in coordination with employees and officials  of other government agencies in the Municipality such as the DepEd and the barangays.

